-- Jordan's Housing Bank reports 16 pct rise in first-half profit
-- By Suleiman Al-Khalidi
-- Sat Jul 26, 2014 09:09AM EDT
-- None



AMMAN, July 26 (Reuters) - Jordan's Housing Bank for Trade and Finance <THBK.AM> posted a 16.4 percent increase in first-half net profit to $86.2 million due to better utilisation of funding in core activities, it said in a statement on Saturday.

Assets stood at $10.7 billion at end of June, up 5 percent from the end of 2013. The bank's main shareholder is Qatar National Bank <QNBK.QA>, with a stake of over 35 percent.